1.What is a server
A server is a powerful computer that provides services or resources to other computers (clients) over a network.

2.What is the role of the domain name
A domain name is a human-readable address used to access a website.

3.What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com
A record points www.foobar.com to an IP address.


4.What is the role of the web server
A web server handles HTTP/HTTPS requests and delivers:
Static contents HTML, CSS, images, JS

5.What is the role of the application server
An application server runs dynamic code (backend logic).
Node.js for JavaScript
PHP-FPM for PHP


6.What is the role of the database
A database stores application data:
MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB


7.What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website
The server communicates with the user's browser over the HTTP(80)/HTTPS(443) protocol using the TCP/IP stack.


8.SPOF(single point of failure).
If any Serevrs becomes unavailable entire website goes down. There is no redundancy.


9. Downtime.
If Server crashes or Network fails The website becomes unavailable. No failover or backup system exists.


10.Scalability.	
When traffic increases Web server queue grows.
A single machine cannot handle high load. You need load balancers, multiple servers, and replication.



